Job responsibility:

To install, maintain and support the IT infrastructure, security, networking, server computers and messaging systems;
Manage Internal IT systems (i.e. web, email, applications and server, etc.); 
Responsible for the installation, administration, maintenance, configuration and support the smooth running of the enterprise network;
Manage infrastructure projects in a quality and timely manner;
Manage system databases and servers to ensure smooth on-going operation and up-time according to service standards.  Plan and perform database version upgrades;
Perform regular network scanning, analysis and threat identification;
Manage and maintain documentation of all IT assets and ensure all processes & procedure are compliant with the company policies;
Manage service transition and release to production process to ensure network infrastructure setup and its components are complied with enterprise technical standard;
Design, deploy, and administer the network infrastructure and supporting systems;
To assist and provide support to solve end user's technical problems including but not limited to any hardware, software and network systems (Operating System, MS Office suite, antivirus, email- client, office printing system, networking, etc.) ;
Provide off-hours operational support for emergency maintenance and deployment events when necessary;

 Job requirement:

Diploma or Degree holders in Computer Science, Information Technology, or related discipline

At least 3-5 years' working experience in server administration and server networking or performing in system support role
Exposure in Live audio/video streaming support will be an advantage
Sound knowledge and technical skills and Microsoft Windows 
Solid experience in Windows Server platform, Active directory, Group Policy, VMare, Networking, Firewall, switch and router
Experience with MacOS will have an added advantage
Willing to provide ad hoc support in non-office hours, if required
Strong problem solving and good interpersonal skills
Interested applicants please send us full CV with current and expected salary and availability.

Benefits : Medical Allowance, Birthday and Childcare Leave 

